Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.03,0:01:34.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Friendship is something that is\Nboth fascinating and beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.43,0:01:38.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was thanks to its power that the boy\Nwas able to escape the bandits' clutches.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.60,0:01:43.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"And yet," my friend said to me, "there is\Nnothing so inconstant as the human heart."
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.00,0:01:48.00,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 3:\N5/22, Stormy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.80,0:02:43.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.97,0:02:46.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wake up!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.14,0:02:54.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe you\nwere still in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.05,0:03:00.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have an important visitor coming today.\NI've been really busy.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.19,0:03:03.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't have to come\nif you don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.49,0:03:05.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the visitor?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.66,0:03:07.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Someone who did me\na favor on Luna.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.46,0:03:11.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that fake Count\nsomething-or-other.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.46,0:03:13.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eugenie! That's going\ntoo far!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.03,0:03:17.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of visitors, Renaud said\nthat he's bringing someone, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.97,0:03:21.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.31,0:03:26.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You know, Albert, you must be\Nthe perfect target for a con artist.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.65,0:03:36.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's losing her temper...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.77,0:03:53.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you angry about?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.44,0:03:56.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who says I'm angry?\NI'm just enjoying our drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.91,0:03:58.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't a race.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.44,0:04:02.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right. You love puttering around\nat a crawl with no destination in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.61,0:04:05.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Both behind the wheel\nand in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.12,0:04:11.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My life is none\nof your business!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.22,0:04:12.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Get out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.16,0:04:14.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sure, just watch me.\NI don't want to ride with you, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.56,0:04:17.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?\NWe're already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.50,0:04:21.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For the life of me, I can't figure\Nout why you and I are engaged!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.30,0:04:23.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Then maybe you should ride\nin Debray's car on the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.97,0:04:28.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.21,0:04:30.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, would you\nbe careful?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.04,0:04:31.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.91,0:04:32.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.24,0:04:37.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Albert!\NCome take a look!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.31,0:04:38.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.58,0:04:43.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Geez, are women all you're good at\Nhandling, Mr. Bigshot private secretary?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.32,0:04:47.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Every dull drive needs a little\nstimulation, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.76,0:04:49.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next to me is a hack\nnewspaper reporter,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.96,0:04:52.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and in the back seat is a couple\nwho just got engaged!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.78,0:05:15.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That was amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.52,0:05:18.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It was nothing. I was in a special\nforces unit in the army.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.76,0:05:22.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Muscle reinforcement processing, huh?\NI'd heard rumors about it...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.29,0:05:24.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your\nassistance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.27,0:05:32.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'll get it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.51,0:05:42.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um... What is your name,\nif I might ask?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.85,0:05:44.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's Valentine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.82,0:05:46.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.72,0:05:53.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Maximilien!\NSorry I'm late!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.32,0:05:58.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There I was, out on recon, and I\nstumbled into an enemy nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.23,0:06:03.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And when I accidentally dropped my\Nfavorite grenade, I went as pale as a ghost!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.97,0:06:09.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,From inside the hole, I could hear the\NErindanians making threatening clicking noises.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.41,0:06:14.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, I don't subscribe to the theory\nthat they're a sentient race.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.58,0:06:18.08,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Would you like a piece?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.47,0:06:18.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In temperament, they're\nvicious and cruel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.68,0:06:19.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.09,0:06:23.65,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I don't want to go into detail\nwith these ladies present,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.09,0:06:27.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but just once, they ought to round up\nthose human rights proponents...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.72,0:06:25.86,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's delicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.99,0:06:30.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and send 'em in there\nto have a nice chat with them!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.73,0:06:31.12,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're a lucky man, Franz!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.80,0:06:35.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Once you're married, you'll be able\nto eat like this every day!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.73,0:06:39.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Um... Where was I?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.80,0:06:42.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right! Just then, I thought\NI was done for!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.07,0:06:45.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And who do you suppose\nshowed up then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.64,0:06:49.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,None other than Space Cavalry\NCaptain Maximilien Morrel,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.88,0:06:51.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...the man I owe\nmy life to!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.65,0:07:00.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite a man to look after a klutz\nwho stumbled his way onto a battlefield.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.96,0:07:03.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you\nhail from?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.83,0:07:06.06,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My family is\nfrom Marseilles.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.30,0:07:08.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's a rough place.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.60,0:07:09.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.80,0:07:13.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Paris, of course!\NAdmittedly, from the old part of town.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.94,0:07:19.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Marseilles... What sort\nof place is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.58,0:07:23.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When I was young, it was\na beautiful harbor town.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.95,0:07:28.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At any rate, it's not a place that\na young lady should venture into.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.84,0:07:51.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We haven't climbed up here\nin a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.74,0:07:53.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What a great breeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.38,0:07:56.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Those clouds look a bit\nmenacing, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.61,0:08:29.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Something interesting\ncatch your eye?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.08,0:08:34.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you suppose there's a need\nto divide the world with city walls?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.18,0:08:37.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The ugliness of the outside world\nexists for the express purpose...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.45,0:08:39.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...of making the beauty of our\Nkingdom stand out all the more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.46,0:08:44.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe, but there's plenty of great\nthings outside the walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.20,0:08:48.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think we should\nopen our eyes a little more?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.43,0:08:51.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, have you grown up a little\nfrom going on your trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.87,0:08:53.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I suppose you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.00,0:08:57.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So go ahead and take on all the troubles\nthat exist outside the walls.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.87,0:09:01.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That should quiet those pangs\Nof boredom of yours a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.88,0:09:05.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That is what we should\nbe looking at.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.08,0:09:08.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The High Court of Justice.\NDanglars Bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.52,0:09:13.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And the place your father works at,\NSpace Forces lmperial Headquarters.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.59,0:09:15.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The triangle of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.73,0:09:19.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That is the true "great thing" that\nwe should inherit, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.37,0:09:28.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To me, it feels like we're the ones\nwho have been sealed in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.92,0:09:46.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am now no longer alone\nin my solitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.79,0:09:51.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For I am now surrounded by the Furies,\nthe goddesses of vengeance.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.66,0:09:56.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In the darkness,\NI awaited the dawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.80,0:10:01.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And once dawn came, I cursed my flesh\nuntil night fell once more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.14,0:10:06.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I even prayed that I would\nlose my sanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.88,0:10:10.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But those prayers\nwent unheeded.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.15,0:10:18.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I even strove for death, but the Devil's\ncold, pitiless hand held me back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.46,0:10:23.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Soon...\NIt won't be long now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.37,0:10:38.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Boy, what a lousy\ndrive that was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.18,0:10:41.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe it was punishment for\Nskipping the Cabinet meeting...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.28,0:10:44.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Have the candidates for the next\NPresident been chosen yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.78,0:10:48.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The word on the street is that\NHis Excellency Morcerf is the front runner.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.49,0:10:51.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've heard a few things from\nyour father, right, Albert?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.16,0:10:55.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Maximilien, you should watch\nyour step around Beauchamp.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.66,0:10:58.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's a terrible man who will use even\nhis friends' scandals as fodder for articles,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.33,0:10:59.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and he won't think twice\nabout it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.96,0:11:02.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's what they call\N"impartial journalism."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.83,0:11:04.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I read your articles\nall the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.07,0:11:07.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But I do not approve\nof the content.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.60,0:11:09.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I get that\nall the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.38,0:11:14.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where are the ladies?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.71,0:11:17.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They went home, saying something\nabout their dresses being soaked.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.28,0:11:19.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Renaud's antique, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.15,0:11:21.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If they'd said something, I would\nhave given them a lift home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.75,0:11:24.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That'd be like tossing food\nto a monkey.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.86,0:11:28.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, the Count of\NMonte Cristo, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.33,0:11:31.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't say that the name\nis familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.29,0:11:33.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There's no documents on him\nat the Cabinet Secretariat, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.70,0:11:36.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably an alias.\NOr maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.40,0:11:38.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A pretender or\na con man, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.44,0:11:42.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll thank you to stop engaging in idle gossip\Nabout an honored guest of the Morcerf home.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.57,0:11:45.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where'd you say that you ran into this\N"honored guest" of yours, again?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.51,0:11:49.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,At Luna's Carnival\nthis past spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.41,0:11:52.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, the honored son of the\nfamily was abducted by bandits.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.82,0:11:57.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's too funny. Were you seduced\nby one of Luna's wily vixens?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.26,0:12:07.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.57,0:12:17.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And that's when the Count rescued me\nfrom their clutches.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.27,0:12:20.21,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you owe him\nyour life, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.48,0:12:24.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's clear that he's incredibly\Nwealthy, as well as very kind.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.08,0:12:30.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And would you say that this millionaire's\nmoney pouch was stuffed full of forged bills?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.15,0:12:31.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.49,0:12:35.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If he wasn't of noble birth, would he\nhave a watch as beautiful as this?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.59,0:12:41.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Con artists use trinkets like that\nall the time to win people's trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.00,0:12:43.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's no con artist!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.07,0:12:45.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He commands a\nhuge spaceship,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.00,0:12:48.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...he travels with aliens and a woman of\nunmatched beauty from Eastern Space,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.37,0:12:51.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...he's free from the rule\nof any government,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.04,0:12:56.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and he mingles freely\nwith people of all classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.55,0:12:59.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In everything he does,\nhe breaks with tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.55,0:13:02.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And then,\nonce night falls,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.49,0:13:05.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...he wanders the darkness in search\nof the lifeblood of beautiful maidens.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.22,0:13:08.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't be surprised\nif he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.23,0:13:13.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Count has a ruthless side that\Ndoesn't care about human life at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.30,0:13:14.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Franz!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.94,0:13:25.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down, Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.48,0:13:31.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You know, there was a case of a sailor who\ncontracted a local disease on some planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.95,0:13:34.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and went around sucking all the\nblood he could find, wasn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.35,0:13:37.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You should be careful,\ntoo, Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.39,0:13:40.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I hear they prefer the blood\nof virgin girls and boys.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.32,0:13:42.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You think he's a vampire or something?\NThat's ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.73,0:13:44.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a lot more plausible\nthan Lunar bandits.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.93,0:13:47.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Or kindhearted\nrich people.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.43,0:13:54.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,His Excellency, the Count\nof Monte Cristo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.04,0:14:02.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Show him in\nat once.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.51,0:14:38.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I beg your pardon.\NThe door was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.68,0:14:41.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's an honor to\nsee you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.79,0:14:45.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The honor is all mine,\NViscount Morcerf.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.69,0:14:47.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Please, call me Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.46,0:14:50.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you and I are on familiar\nterms by now, Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.73,0:14:54.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And now, as promised, allow me\nto introduce you to my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.53,0:14:57.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You already know Franz.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.03,0:15:00.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is Lucien Debray.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.20,0:15:02.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He is a shrewd civil servant, who already holds\na key position in the Interior Ministry...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.71,0:15:04.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...in spite of his\nyoung age.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.61,0:15:06.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is Beauchamp.\NHe's a newspaper reporter.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.41,0:15:10.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He can tell you anything you\nmight want to know about Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.35,0:15:14.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Admittedly, it's more of a third-rate\ngossip sheet than a newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.25,0:15:16.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Most fascinating.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.79,0:15:21.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Cavalry Captain Maximilien Morrel,\nhero of the Eridanus campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.86,0:15:23.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.33,0:15:26.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, the very paragon of a\Nfaithful, brave soldier, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.60,0:15:29.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You know the Captain?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.80,0:15:31.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.33,0:15:35.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,We've heard that you've come to us\nfrom somewhere far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.37,0:15:37.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're trying to interview him already?\NDon't be rude to our guest.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.01,0:15:40.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm just doing\nmy job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.48,0:15:47.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,On many worlds, photographs are\nseen as an abominable custom.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.48,0:15:49.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I must ask you\nto abstain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.59,0:15:51.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, sorry...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.49,0:15:54.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In the course of visiting many\Nforeign lands as a sailor,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.02,0:15:58.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...l've become thoroughly tainted\nby the customs of other worlds.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.16,0:16:03.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I must seem quite the savage\nto the people of Paris.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.17,0:16:06.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What sorts of places\nhave you been to?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.37,0:16:08.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I have traveled\nto many places.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.31,0:16:14.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To Eastern Space. To Northern Space.\NEven to the core of the galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.38,0:16:16.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even the lmperium?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.55,0:16:20.68,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. To a sailor, there\Nare no such things as borders.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.05,0:16:23.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Could that not be considered\ntreason against the state?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.99,0:16:28.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see no reason to swear loyalty to people\nwho do nothing to protect me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.06,0:16:30.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you not agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.13,0:16:33.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see you possess\nrather bold opinions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.43,0:16:35.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,True enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.23,0:16:41.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I suggest that you experience being cast out\ninto the vast universe all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.47,0:16:45.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I expect that you will soon understand that the\nonly person one can count upon is oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.38,0:16:52.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Set the table for tea\nat once.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.25,0:16:58.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And where do you\nhail from?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.56,0:17:04.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I came into this world in a land\Nthat is beyond your imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.16,0:17:08.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A place that you'd rather\nnot mention?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.60,0:17:12.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Franz!\NDon't be rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.57,0:17:17.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If we're going to be associating as friends,\nshouldn't we at least know that much?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.21,0:17:18.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That is quite understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.91,0:17:23.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The reason that distinguished gentlemen\nsuch as yourselves are interested in me...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.48,0:17:26.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...is because of the air of mystery\nsurrounding me, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.42,0:17:30.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Were that not the case, surely a rustic\naristocrat from the frontiers of space...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.79,0:17:33.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...would not have been given\na seat at your table.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.13,0:17:38.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you have us there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.30,0:17:43.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But that's exactly why we want\nto know more about you, Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.53,0:17:45.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're as naive as ever, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.67,0:17:49.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Peppo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.11,0:17:51.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is something\nthe matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.27,0:17:53.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Um, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.00,0:18:17.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All right, what are you\nup to?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.57,0:18:19.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You caught me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.44,0:18:22.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I quit the bandit gang.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.84,0:18:26.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So I came here to Paris\nto look for work.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.54,0:18:28.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But what are you\ndoing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.85,0:18:31.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I followed you here, Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.62,0:18:34.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm lying, I'm lying!\NIt's just a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.95,0:18:36.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There happened to be an\nopening here, that's all.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.09,0:18:38.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, Peppo...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.09,0:18:41.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, you remembered\nmy name.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.23,0:18:44.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you planning to\nstay here for good?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.46,0:18:45.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Can't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.73,0:18:47.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's,\nhow can I put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.87,0:18:52.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. Let's just agree to\nkeep each other's secrets, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.47,0:18:59.10,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you interested in learning\nthat man's real identity?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.48,0:19:03.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry about it too much.\NHe's nobody special.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.61,0:19:07.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want to do tonight?\NHit up Le Queen?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.48,0:19:09.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay,\NI'll pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.69,0:19:11.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As will I.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.29,0:19:14.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck\nis this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.93,0:19:18.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The Count of\NMonte Cristo's voice...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.66,0:19:20.13,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.83,0:19:22.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't on the recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.30,0:19:25.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What sorts of places\nhave you been to?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.97,0:19:29.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even the lmperium?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.64,0:19:35.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Some might see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.31,0:19:36.34,count alt,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably a\nmechanical malfunction.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.48,0:19:38.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, is this a\nmalfunction, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.23,0:19:56.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What a beautiful woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.77,0:19:58.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,T-That's my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.04,0:20:02.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She is rather young.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.44,0:20:06.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This vista is that of Marseilles,\nis it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.51,0:20:11.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She likes paintings like this. I don't know\nwhy she chose that place as the setting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.18,0:20:13.17,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It is magnificent.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.28,0:20:15.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, my father hates\nthis painting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.02,0:20:19.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He was going to take it down and burn it, but\nwe placated him by hanging it in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.23,0:20:24.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Edmond...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.36,0:20:28.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is there something\nabout this painting?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.66,0:20:31.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No. I'm afraid that it is time\nthat I took my leave of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.97,0:20:35.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't say that! Please,\nhave dinner with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.67,0:20:38.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My mother and father are looking forward\nto meeting you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.28,0:20:44.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you're interested in paintings, my mother and\nfather have many others in their collection.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.89,0:20:52.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My, what a stirring\npainting this is.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.39,0:20:53.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This is what\nmy father likes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.06,0:20:56.92,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The ones that my mother has collected\nare over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.50,0:21:04.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This must be\nyour visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.96,0:23:12.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My mother's past,\nwhich I never knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.20,0:23:14.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The men\nin her past.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.70,0:23:16.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Adults who live\nin the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.83,0:23:19.46,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 4:\NA Mother's Secrets
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.03,0:23:19.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Gankutsuou,\NThe Count of Monte Cristo, act 4,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.40,0:23:20.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,..."A Mother's Secrets".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.87,0:23:23.03,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time,\nand hold out hope!
